  "text": "where E (t) is a vector of multivariate zero-mean uncorrelated white noise process and Λ (r) is the N ×N matrices of model coefficients, the dimension p in the model can be estimated using the Akaike criterion, while the values of coefficients in Eq. (2) can be obtained by the Nuttall-Strand method, which is reported to be the best one among multivariate autoregressive estimators [CITATION_1] . In order to investigate the spectral properties of the examined process, Eq. (2) is transformed to the frequency domain.",
